Description: Night light / red tint for the COSMIC desktop
 A night-light utility for the COSMIC desktop (Pop!_OS) that warms the screen
 color temperature on a schedule.
 .
 COSMIC's compositor does not yet expose a gamma-control Wayland protocol, so
 this package writes the gamma ramp directly to the kernel's DRM/KMS layer. A
 small privileged helper (run via polkit/pkexec) briefly switches virtual
 terminals so the compositor releases the DRM master lock, applies the gamma
 LUTs to every active display, and switches back; the tint then persists.
 .
 Ships a libcosmic GUI, a background scheduler (systemd user service), and the
 polkit rule that lets desktop users apply the tint without a password prompt.

